1944;;Man of Evil;;British;;Anthony Asquith;;James Mason, Phyllis Calvert, Stewart Granger;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_of_Evil;;Fanny (Phyllis Calvert) finishes at boarding school in 1880 and returns to London, where she witnesses Lord Manderstoke (James Mason) fight and kill her supposed father. She soon learns that her family has run a brothel next door to her home and (on her mother's death) that he was not her real father. She goes to meet her real father – a respected politician – and falls in love with Harry Somerford (Stewart Granger), his advisor. Manderstoke continues to thwart her happiness.